The '''[[Collectivity of Saint Martin]]''' ({{lang-fr|CollectivitÃ© de Saint-Martin}}) is an [[overseas collectivity]] of [[France]] located in the [[Leeward Islands]] of the [[Lesser Antilles]] [[archipelago]] in the [[Caribbean Sea]].<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook>{{cite web|date=July 2, 2009|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/rn.html|title=Saint Martin|work=[[The World Factbook]]|publisher=[[United States]] [[Central Intelligence Agency]]|accessdate=July 23, 2009}}</ref> It came into being on February 22, 2007, encompassing the northern parts of the [[Saint Martin|island of Saint Martin]] and neighbouring [[islet]]s, the largest of which is [[Ãle Tintamarre]]. The southern part of the island, [[Sint Maarten]], is a constituent country of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]].
